    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it law that all dogs must be on a lead no longer that 1.5m around livestock",
        "additional_details": "Too many lambs and sheep get killed or injured by dogs. The owners may believe they have control or recall when actually they don\u2019t. It takes 10 seconds to put a dog on a lead. Dog owners should not be allowed to keep their dog under \"close control\", they should be required to use a lead. Something needs to be done to help save the lives of the animals and save the farming industry money.",
        "background": "With so many dog owners being irresponsible and failing to prevent dogs chasing and even killing livestock it needs to be clear cut that dogs should be on a lead (no longer than 1.5m) when in a field with livestock.",
